com.avaya.csta.binding

Class GetAgentStateResponsePrivateData

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.GetAgentStateResponsePrivateData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GetAgentStateResponsePrivateData
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Avaya extensions to GetAgentStateResponse.

    The parameters for GetAgentStateResponsePrivateData are:

    GetAgentStateResponse Response Parameters
    workMode WorkMode The agent work mode as defined by Communication Manager. Valid values are:
    • AUTOIN: Indicates that the agent is allowed to receive a new call immediately after disconnecting from the previous call. The talkState parameter indicates whether the agent is busy or idle.
    • MANUALIN: Indicates that the agent is automatically changed to the AFTERCALLWORK work mode immediately after disconnecting from the previous call.
    • AFTERCALLWORK: Indicates that the agent is in the agent state AGENTWORKINGAFTERCALL.
    • AUXWORK: Indicates that the agent is in the agent state AGENTNOTREADY.
    talkState TalkState Provides actual readiness of the agent. Valid values are:
    • ONCALL: Indicates agent is occupied with serving a call.
    • IDLE: Indicates agent is ready to accept calls.
    reasonCode integer Specifies the reason for change of work mode to AUXWORK or the logged-out state. The valid range of reason codes is 0-99. A value of zero indicates the reasonCode is not available. The meaning of codes 1-99 is defined by the application.
    pendingReasonCode integer Specifies the pending reason code which will take effect when the agent gets off the call. A value of 0 indicates that the pending reason code is not available.
    Version:
    $Revision$ $Date$
